code editors -> VS code, sublime text, brackets, vim, emacs and alot more. (front-end)

HTML -> hyper text markup language. (used for structering / skeleton)

There are two types of tags:
1. Opening-closing tags (90%)
2. Non-closing tags (10%)

<p> ->  paragraph tag Opening tag
</p> -> paragraph tag Closing tag

<br> ->  break line

<a href, target> -> anchor tag href and target are attributes.

h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6 -> heading 

hr -> horizontal line.

img -> for putting images into our file.

four main types of sending data to the server:
1. get request -> give me data ()
2. post request -> take data from me.
3. put request -> take data from me and update if their is no\existing data data (update).
4. delete request -> delete the data which i am requesting to.

LIST TYPES
* Unordered lists

* Ordered List


All HTML elements will have these two attributes -> class, id (they are kind of hooks to gather that tag.)

CSS DISPLAY

1) Inline
2) Block
3) inline-block (custom DISPLAY Style)

Width and heigth according to screen size.
1) width -> vw
2) heigth -> vh


HOW TO NAME VARIABLES.
1) Kebab Case: box-little-goes-here.
2) Snake Case: box_little_goes_here.
3) Camel Case: boxLittleGoesHere.


FLEX CHEETSHEET
for row -> justify-content
for col -> align-content


TO SET A LINE FOR ELEMENTS TO HANG ON.
-> align-items

====================================================================================

Terminal command line.
=> How to open cmd.

1. Desktop -> press shift and right click.
2. search in windows.
3. if you are in any folder -> ctrl+L, and then type cmd.

=> Folder Navigation
to get in -> cd folderName
to get out -> cd ..
to clear cmd -> cls(windows) / clear (mac)
to view all the files -> dir (windows) / ls (mac)
to delete a file -> rm
rm -rf -> joke

====================================================================

GIT basics

there are 2 things, 1) git, 2) github
1) git-> it is versioning control system (VCS).
2) github-> it is website where whole code lives.

USAGE.

we have to download git into our system to use it.

git status -> to check the status of folder.

git add -> start tracking all the files.
git commit -> save all the changes.
git push -u origin master -> push all the code to the github.

git add -> git commit -> git push -u orgin master.

